= El abrazo

It arrives without a meeting, because it no longer needs one: the realization, assembling itself across a season of small facts, that the Movement has become *manageable* — and that the system knows it. The invitations arrive before the requests now. The posts renew themselves. The confrontations are scheduled, like maintenance. Somewhere in the last few years the antechambers stopped being enemy territory and became, in the file's own serene annotation, *interlocutores responsables.*

This is the embrace. It is warm, it is generous, and it is how the system has ended every opposition it could not shoot: not with a betrayal but with a thousand reasonable accommodations, each one defensible, the sum of which is a tame left that delivers its sector on schedule — a PPS with better martyrs.

There is still time to be something else. Barely, and at a price.

- @romper_abrazo: Break it. Walk out of the antechambers loudly — back to the political road, the plazas, the enemy's honest hatred.
- @aceptar_abrazo: Stay. Inside is where the budgets are; history can be moved in millimeters; someone must be at the table.

@romper_abrazo
go-to: post_event
choose-if: unity >= 40
unavailable-subtitle: Walking out takes a party united enough to survive the funcionarios' resignations — yours is not.
on-arrival: {!
Q.via = "politica";
Q.absorcion = 25;
Q.pri_reformist_rel -= 15;
Q.funds -= 5;
Q.sup_students += 4;
Q.sup_workers += 2;
Q.unity -= 4;
Q.political_capital += 3;
Q.fe_voto += 2;
!}

The rupture is performed in public, because only public things are irreversible: the posts resigned in one coordinated week, the letter read from the tribune naming exactly what was offered and what it cost, the antechambers' hospitality returned unconsumed. A third of the placed cadres refuse to come out — the stomach keeps what it has digested — and the relationships of a decade close like doors down a corridor. What walks out is smaller, poorer, and unmistakably alive. In the colonias they say it plainly: *volvieron.* They came back.

@aceptar_abrazo
go-to: post_event
on-arrival: absorcion = 85; funds += 6; political_capital += 3; sup_students -= 6; sup_workers -= 3; fe_voto -= 3; guerrilla_meter += 3; fac_nueva_izquierda -= 6

The decision is never announced because it was never exactly made: the Movement simply continues, inside, reasonable, funded, consulted — and the country files it accordingly. The young go elsewhere: to the coordinadoras, to the new little parties, some to the mountains, taking with them the future's energy and leaving the apparatus's calm. The system has added one more instrument to its orchestra. It plays, from now on, mostly on schedule.
